result.execSummary:
The defendant Anna G. McDaniel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant shall submit to a DNA sample at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $50.00 a month beginning June 6, 2016.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Anna McDaniel in court. Defendant states she is able to pay the amount owed today on her worthless check. So ordered by the court. DE requests an extension in her payment plan to skip her August payment. Court approves that request; her payments are to resume 9-16-16. ap
contempt of court; issuance of worthless check to the court
Request for Payment Plan, Agreement to Make Payments, and Order

Defendant Anna G. McDaniel in court.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea agreement put into the record.  Defendant freely and voluntarily waives right to an attorney.  Plea of guilty.  Plea colloquy.  Plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently; factual basis exists. Court finds defendant guilty and orders court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.  The costs are to be paid at the rate of $50.00 a month beginning June 6, 2016.  Appeal rights given to defendant.  - rt
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 25, 2016 at 01:00 pm.
Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

Defendant Anna G. McDaniel in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Waive reading of complaint, charges and penalties. Plea of not guilty to the charge.   Court orders $500.00 signature bond; booking and no possession or consumption of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 14, 2016 at 11:30 am.  - rt

*Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the Court.  Must report to the Taylor County Sheriff's Office for Booking Procedure.  Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.
